header.gameNote: COLLEGE OF CHARLESTON CLASSIC AT CHARLESTON SC

article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 61, IUPUI 58
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Manny Ubilla had 14 points and seven rebounds to help Fairleigh Dickinson to a 61-58 win over IUPUI in the opening round of the College of Charleston Holiday Classic on Friday night. Michael Peeples broke a tie with two free throws with eight seconds left to give the Knights (6-5) a 60-58 lead. Peeples then blocked a shot at the other end and Ubilla hit one of two free throws with a second to go to seal the win. The Jaguars led for most of the second half before the Knights tied it at 50 with just under six minutes to go on Ubilla's jumper. Neither team would lead by more than three for the rest of the way. Andre Harris and Sean Baptiste each scored 13 points and each pulled down nine rebounds for Fairleigh Dickinson. George Hill led IUPUI with 19 points and 15 rebounds, while David Barlow added 12 points for the Jaguars.
